author: COMSOL
description:
A 3D supersonic flow enters a channel at Mach 1.4. The flow hits an obstacle at the bottom of the channel, and shock waves are created. The shock waves propagate through the fluid and diffract at the channel walls. The flow is assumed to be compressible and inviscid.

The model makes use of the adaptive mesh refinement feature in COMSOL Multiphysics. This example is based on a 2D case that has been widely used in earlier studies of inviscid compressible flow.
